message.content:
cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DB, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on offloading cellular traffic onto D2D sharing among users in proximity, utilizing wireless short-range D2D communications for sharing contents locally. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the social impacts of D2D sharing among friends and analyzes social arborescence as one of the multidimensional features. 
- cs.SOC (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper touches upon privacy preservation policies in D2D sharing. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a likely category as the paper proposes to design a big data platform, named D2D Big Data, to encourage wireless D2D communications among users effectively and to carry out offloading intelligence for operators efficiently. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper briefly mentions privacy preservation policies and may touch upon security issues related to D2D sharing.
